Description: Faience fragment of vase or plaque, with remains of figure in high relief. A foot and lower leg raised as if walking to left, with glaze surface worn off. Background retains glaze. Along straight base is an inset groove, ground line (?), on which figure is walking/dancing. Glaze colour, bluish green, core - yellowish, fine texture.
Curator's comments: Cf. with similar fragment in AES 86.0401.1502 68830 which has booted foot, knee and lower thigh preserved.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (FD.07)
